                    <span>This appears to be a book rushed into print by Earl Woods and a ghostwriter, written just around the time of Earl's bypass surgery.  The book is very shallow and doesn't address any of the interesting milestones of Tiger's golf development.  Nor does it deal with any interesting personal issues - i.e. how did he deal with losses, how did he relate to his peers in school, etc.  I would not recommend this boo</span>
                  
              
